==English==

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|keh₂p}}
First attested in the late 14th century, from {{bor|en|fro|acceptable|notext=1}}, from {{der|en|LL.|acceptābilis||worthy of acceptance}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/æk.ˈsɛp.tə.bəl/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-acceptable.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# [[worthy]], [[decent]], sure of being [[accept]]ed or received with at least moderate [[pleasure]]
#: ''We need to find an ''acceptable'' present for Jeff.''
# Barely worthy, less than excellent; [[passable]].
#: ''The designs were '''acceptable''', but they were nothing special either.''

